Full Job Description

** This position can be 100% Remote **


Essential Duties and Responsibilities

ASL Video - https://vimeo.com/734406023/e11df512c0

  • Design, code and integrate software for embedded Linux and Android targets
  • Validate, optimize Android BSP drivers, performance, and footprint
  • Improve and maintain existing software components
  • Write unit and system tests to validate software components
  • Work with security team to implement security features of Android BSP and applications


Knowledge/Skills/Abilities Required

ASL Video - https://vimeo.com/734406738/f8526a6b1b

  • Embedded Linux software development including BSP and drivers
  • Familiarity with Android security model (SE Linux policy) and secure boot
  • Experience with Google’s AOSP architecture developing Android frameworks
  • Android Native applications (JNI/NDK) experience
  • Strong C /C++ programming skills
  • Experience in Linux Kernel and Android Software Development
  • Experience with ARM processors and/or embedded software development on mobile or embedded devices
  • Experience with multi-core, multi-threading, memory tracking development and debugging
  • Excellent written and verbal communication skills
  • Experience with Wi-Fi, SIP or VoIP a plus


Qualifications

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Information Systems, or related field.

2+ years experience

Privacy Preference Center

Indeed may store or retrieve information on your browser, mostly in the form of cookies. Cookies are text-only pieces of information that a website transfers to an individual’s hard drive or other website-browsing equipment for record-keeping purposes. Cookies allow Indeed to remember important information that will make your use of the site more convenient and give you a more personalised web experience. If a toggle is present, if you toggle to the right, that would enable these cookies to be placed.
Cookie and Privacy Policy

Manage Consent Preferences

Strictly Necessary Cookies

Always Active

These cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be switched off in our systems. They are usually only set in response to actions made by you which amount to a request for services, such as setting your privacy preferences, logging in or filling in forms. You can set your browser to block or alert you about these cookies, but some parts of the site will not then work.

Performance Cookies

Always Active

These cookies allow us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve the performance of our site. They help us to know which pages are the most and least popular and see how visitors move around the site. If you do not allow these cookies we will not know when you have visited our site, and will not be able to monitor its performance.

Functional Cookies

Always Active

These cookies enable the website to provide enhanced functionality and personalisation. They may be set by us or by third party providers whose services we have added to our pages.    If you do not allow these cookies then some or all of these services may not function properly.

Targeting Cookies

These cookies may be set through our site by our advertising partners. They may be used by those companies to build a profile of your interests and show you relevant adverts on other sites. They do not store directly personal information, but are based on uniquely identifying your browser and internet device. If you do not allow these cookies, you will experience less targeted advertising. Special notes for iOS App: If viewed in native mobile app, your data will not be shared with third party sites for tracking across third party apps or sites. We will not display targeted advertisements in your app or share your information with other apps.

Google “NID” cookie 'advertising and preference’ purposes

These cookies may be set through our site by Google where you consent to it They may be used by Google to build a profile of your interests and show you relevant adverts on other sites. If you do not allow this cookie, you may not be able to use Google log in methods such as OneTap
